name: Succulent
description: Succulents are low-maintenance plants that store water in their leaves, making them ideal for dry climates.

name: Basil
description: Basil is a fragrant herb commonly used in cooking. It requires warm weather and regular watering.

name: Cactus
description: Cacti are hardy plants that thrive in arid conditions. They require minimal water and are easy to care for.

name: Mini Tomato
description: Mini tomato plants produce small, flavorful tomatoes and need plenty of sunlight and water.

name: Rosemary
description: Rosemary is an aromatic herb that is used in cooking and has a lovely fragrance. It prefers sunny, well-drained areas.

name: Lavender
description: Lavender is known for its beautiful purple flowers and calming scent. It thrives in sunny, dry areas.

name: Janda Bolong
description: Janda Bolong, or Monstera Adansonii, is a popular houseplant known for its unique, holey leaves.

name: Mint
description: Mint is a versatile herb that grows quickly and spreads easily. It needs plenty of water and can tolerate partial shade.

name: Thyme
description: Thyme is a hardy herb that is used in cooking. It prefers sunny spots and well-drained soil.

name: Parsley
description: Parsley is a popular culinary herb that needs regular watering and plenty of sunlight.

name: Chives
description: Chives are easy to grow and are commonly used in cooking. They need regular watering and plenty of sunlight.
